    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="767"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d767">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/23452c.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Special Commissioners</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 21, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In view of the commanding position the Constitutionalists have secured in Mexico
                    and the necessity of considering the views of those whom they represent, the
                    President suggests that you ask the Mediators whether they do not consider it
                    advisable to renew the invitation to the Constitutionalists to send
                    commissioners without attempting to define the scope of what is to be discussed
                    and without reference to <pb facs="0620" n="504" xml:id="pg_504"/> the
                    suspension of hostilities. It is likely to involve many delays and uncertainties
                    if the discussion is conducted without them, and it is extremely difficult to
                    confer with them satisfactorily by indirect ways such as are open to us
                    here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
